quizzes.textContent:
[h1]transform-origin[/h1]

The [b]transform-origin[/b] property allows you to change the position of transformed elements. The default value for the property is 50% 50%, which corresponds to the center of the element.
In the example below, we use the [b]transform-origin[/b] property together with [b]transform-rotate[/b]. The origin of the x-axis (horizontal) is set to 25% from the left. The origin for the y-axis (vertical) is set to 75% from above.

[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="625"]div.empty-div {
   position: relative;
   height: 100px;
   width: 100px;
   margin: 30px;
   padding: 10px;
   border: 1px solid black;
}
div.green-div {
   padding: 50px;
   position: absolute;
   background-color: #8bc34a;
   border: 1px solid white;
   transform: rotate(15deg);
   [b]transform-origin: 25% 75%;[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2710" width="100%"]
[note][b]0 0[/b] is the same value as [b]top left[/b], and [b]100% 100%[/b] is the same value as [b]bottom right[/b].
The transform-origin property must be used together with the transform property.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Add a translate function that moves the element 50 pixels from the left and 100 pixels from the top.
[!raw!]
transform: {0} ({1}px, {2}px);

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The translate() Method[/h1]

The [b]translate() [/b]method moves an element from its current position (according to the parameters given for the x-axis and the y-axis). Positive values will push an element down and to the right of its default position, while negative values will pull an element up and to the left of its default position.

In this example below, the div element is moved [b]100px to the right[/b] and [b]50px down:[/b][code format="css" codeId="626"]div {
   padding: 50px;
   position: absolute;
   background-color: #32CD32;
   [b]transform:translate(100px, 50px);[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2711" width="100%"]
[note]An element can also be moved by setting the margins or by positioning the element, although translate is a better choice for animating elements.[/note]
